PHASE 2 — CODE FIXES (All Committed & Pushed to main)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

COMMIT a754696 — Redis guard (customsready/app/queue.server.ts)
  Problem:  ioredis was still instantiated even when REDIS_URL absent — crash
            on Netlify cold start.
  Fix:      Wrapped entire Redis instantiation in `if (process.env.REDIS_URL)`.
            Added error event listener. Removed `!` non-null assertion.

COMMIT f4a5a15 — Remove headers exports from all 6 apps
  Problem:  `export const headers: HeadersFunction` crashes Remix SSR when
            headersArgs is undefined (loader failure / redirect).
  Files:    Craftline/app/routes/app.tsx
            FixitCSV/app/routes/app.tsx
            Stagewise/app/routes/app.tsx
            apps/poref-new/app/routes/app.tsx
            apps/quoteloop-new/app/routes/app.tsx
            customsready/app/root.tsx  ← script incorrectly targeted root.tsx
  Also:     Removed HeadersFunction imports + orphaned boundary imports.

COMMIT 403ebd3 — Fix trailing comma in customsready/app/root.tsx
  Problem:  Removal script left `ScrollRestoration,  }` — TS syntax error
            prevented module compilation, entire route tree failed to mount.
  Fix:      Cleaned the import line.

COMMIT b52360c — Restore customsready/app/root.tsx to minimal Remix root
  Problem:  root.tsx had extraneous loader + addDocumentResponseHeaders.
  Fix:      Replaced entire file with clean minimal Remix root:
              Links, Meta, Outlet, Scripts, ScrollRestoration only.
              No loader, no custom headers.

COMMIT 084a101 — Fix customsready/app/routes/_index.tsx
  Problem:  Previous fix used authenticate.admin() in _index — wrong.
  Fix:      Redirect-only logic, required default export for Remix route manifest:
              ?shop → /auth/login
              else  → /app

COMMIT 87e41ae — Remove basename from customsready/vite.config.ts
  Root cause of "No route matches URL /":
    `basename: "/customsready"` shifted ALL routes off the domain root:
      _index.tsx  registered as /customsready  (not /)
      app.tsx     registered as /customsready/app  (not /app)
  Fix:      Removed `basename: "/customsready"` from the remix() plugin call.

COMMIT 3370b54 — Separate auth routes
  Problem:  /auth/login was calling authenticate.admin() — Shopify SDK error.
  Fix:      Created auth.login.tsx with loader → login(request) only.
            Note: shopify.server.ts exports `login` as named export (line 97).

COMMIT e00562d — Restore auth.login.tsx with full form UI + action
  Problem:  auth.login.tsx had no default export — Remix treated it as a
            resource route and returned `{}` JSON instead of rendering a page.
  Fix:      Added:
            - action: reads shop from FormData, appends to URL, calls login()
            - default export AuthLogin(): renders shop domain input form with
              error display and loading state
  Result:   /auth/login now renders an install form and triggers Shopify OAuth.

